lll_multird:%0 has been given more than one initial ram disc
lll_multikernel:%0 has been given more than one kernel
lll_bootfail:Boot failed for unknown reason
lll_anykey:Press almost any key exit
lll_nokernel:%0 must be given a kernel
lll_help:Linloader boots Linux/ARM. The following options are supported:|J|J  -k, --kernel           RISC OS filename of the kernel to be booted, if this|J                          option is omitted the first non-option argument is|J                          used as the kernel filename.|J  -i, --initrd           RISC OS filename of the initial ram disc (initrd) to|J                          be loaded, alternatively a initial ram disc may be|J                          specified by a argument beginning "initrd=".|J  -c, --no-clear         Do not clear the screen.|J  -q, --quiet            Do not display banner.|J  -e, --extra-arguments  Prompt for extra kernel arguments before clearing the|J                          screen or displaying the banner.|J      --dry-run          Do a dry run, do not actually boot the kernel.|J  -h, --help             Show this help text.|J      --credits          Show credits.|J|JNote that Linloader does not (yet) shut down the desktop so all unsaved|Jwork will be lost. Linloader is © 1999 Timothy Baldwin and others, and is|Jreleased under the GNU GPL.|J
